            <div type="translation">
                <p> <lb n="1"/>Having been blessed in life with many good things
                    <lb n="2"/>of which thou, O Virgin, wast seen to be the provider,
                    <lb n="3"/>I, Nikephoros magistros, a pitiable supplicant,
                    <lb n="4"/>erected this church with devotion,
                    <lb n="5"/>in return for which I beg to find thee my protectress
                    <lb n="6"/>on the terrible day of judgment. (after <ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 79)</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscriprion is thought to copy an earlier, twelfth-century dedicatory inscription in this position. According to <ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 79, linguistic parallels with other twelfth-century dedicatory inscriptions in Cyprus and Greece support this interpretation.</p>
            </div>
